div.div: Commented on #717 Authorization Token fill not working (electron)

official client doesn't store token in LocalStorage It stores token in localStorage, however it is only accessible before the page unload trigger event. If you reload the page with localStorage on devtools open, you can notice how the token briefly appears. In any case, MV2 browsers can fetch it, but MV3 can't :-/
undiscord already circumvents the unload trigger event, when I reverse engineered discord years ago. this is about the native electron client, not the browser.
Commented on #717 Authorization Token fill not working

official client doesn't store token in LocalStorage, last time I checked this it was stored in the electron background process and wasn't accessible in the renderer/ui process. This was the roadblock when I was making the betterdiscord pluggin here https://github.com/victornpb/undiscord/pull/357 checking now seems like some people posted workarounds but they are untested
